cs.CG, cs.DS, cs.DM, cs.CC, cs.GT 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper deals with straight-line drawings of graphs in the Euclidean plane and the concept of increasing-chord paths and trees. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper discusses the complexity of determining the existence of increasing-chord spanning trees rooted at a given vertex. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is relevant as the paper deals with graph theory and combinatorics. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper proves the NP-completeness of the problem of determining the existence of increasing-chord spanning trees rooted at a given vertex. 
- cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses a reduction from the 3-SAT problem, which is a well-known problem in game theory.
